# Windows Credential Manager is the default secret store (see CLAUDE.md /
# AgentColabPlan.md "Credentials & tenant isolation"). This .env file is an
# explicit FALLBACK ONLY, and the runner refuses to start if it is readable
# by any account other than the current user.
#
# Never put a raw secret in project.md, spec.md, or anywhere under projects/ —
# those files store opaque aliases only (e.g. `gsc: acme-gsc-readonly`), and
# the alias is resolved to a real credential at connector-call time, never
# logged, and always passed through tools/lib/redact.py before anything
# touches disk.
#
# Example (fallback mode only — prefer Credential Manager):
# ACME_GSC_READONLY=
# ACME_DATAFORSEO_READ=
